cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ai-literature-os: a reference implementation of an AI-augmented scientific literature operating system"
message: "If you find this useful and want to cite it, please use the metadata below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Morrison
    given-names: Christopher
abstract: >
  A reference implementation of an AI-augmented scientific literature workflow.
  Coordinates QMD (vector + keyword search), PaperQA2 (passage-grounded synthesis),
  Docling (PDF conversion), Claude Code (agentic skills), and OpenRouter
  (embeddings + scoring) into a single system. Components: a vault pipeline that
  ingests, enriches, embeds, and clusters a personal markdown evidence vault; an
  optional research digest that polls PubMed, bioRxiv, and NIH Reporter and scores
  results against a researcher profile; Claude Code skills for fast search, deep
  synthesis, and paper intake; and a librarian agent that audits pipeline health.
  Shared as a reference implementation, not a maintained product.
repository-code: "https://github.com/topher1010/ai-literature-os"
